history.content:
I managed to get into 189 and 186 this semester after the first week as an undeclared student.

I was able to get into CS 170, 168, 161, and 169 undeclared. CS 188 as well, but it was a much more difficult process that required appealing to L&S since they closed the waitlist early. I've tried multiple times to get into 160 and failed so 160 is very unlikely. The (major) key is to take classes that are either unpopular or have an unpopular professor that semester, to try for the discussion with the shortest waitlist, and to do everything in the class as if you're already enrolled.

I won't be declared until the end of Fall semester, but due to my tight graduation plan, I really need to take an upper division CS class that semester. Problem is, since I won't be declared, I bet it'll be very hard to get off the waitlists for those classes.

I know CS 170 and 188 are easy to get into non-declared, but other than those two classes, are there any CS upper division classes a non-declared student can get into? Would 160 be possible to get into?
